13 PART III. DEPARTMENT OF REVENUE AUTHORIZATION TO FORCE COLLECT
14 DEBTS
15 SECTION 11.(a) Chapter 105A of the General Statutes reads as rewritten:
16 "Chapter 105A.
17 "Setoff Debt Collection and Forced Debt Collection Act.
18 "Article 1.
19 "In General.
20 "§ 105A-1. Purposes.
21 The purpose of this Chapter is to establish as policy that all claimant agencies agencies, the
22 Office of the State Auditor, and the Department of Revenue shall cooperate in identifying debtors
23 who owe money to the State or to a local government through their various agencies and who
24 qualify for refunds from the Department of Revenue. agencies. It is also the intent of this Chapter
25 that procedures be established for (i) setting off against any a debtor's tax refund the sum of any
26 debt owed to the State or to a local government. government and (ii) force collecting debts owed
27 to State agencies. Furthermore, it is the legislative intent that this Chapter be liberally construed
28 so as to effectuate these purposes as far as legally and practically possible.
29 "§ 105A-2. Definitions.
30 The following definitions apply in this Chapter:
31 …
32 (5) Forced collection. – The debt collection remedies provided by G.S. 105A-6B
33 and G.S. 105A-6C.
34 …
35 (7) Net proceeds collected. – Gross For setoff collection actions, "net proceeds
36 collected" means gross proceeds collected through setoff against a debtor's
37 refund minus the collection assistance fees provided in
38 G.S. 105A-13.G.S. 105A-13(a) or (c), as appropriate. For forced collection
39 actions, "net proceeds collected" means gross proceeds collected through
40 forced collection minus the forced collection assistance fee provided in
