1 (c) Debts Eligible for Forced Collection. – Only those debts that are discovered through
2 an audit or investigation undertaken by the Office of the State Auditor in accordance with
3 G.S. 147-64.6(c)(21) are eligible for forced collection under this Chapter.
4 "§ 105A-6B. Levy and sale.
5 Notwithstanding that a debt owed to a State agency is not a collectible tax under
6 G.S. 105-241.22, if a debtor does not pay a debt, or enter into an installment agreement to pay a
7 debt, within 60 days of being notified by the Department in accordance with G.S. 105A-6A(b),
8 the Department may force collect the debt by levy and sale in the manner prescribed by
9 G.S. 105-242(a)(1) and (a)(2) for the levy and sale of property for the nonpayment of tax.
10 "§ 105A-6C. Attachment and garnishment.
11 Notwithstanding that a debt owed to a State agency is not a collectible tax under
12 G.S. 105-241.22, if a debtor does not pay a debt, or enter into an installment agreement to pay a
13 debt, within 60 days of being notified by the Department in accordance with G.S. 105A-6A(b),
14 the Department may force collect the debt by attachment and garnishment in the manner
15 prescribed by G.S. 105-242.1 for the attachment and garnishment of intangible personal property
16 for the nonpayment of tax.
17 "§ 105A-6D. Installment agreements.
18 The Secretary may enter into an agreement with the debtor for payment of the debt in
19 installments if the Secretary determines that the agreement will facilitate collection of the debt.
20 The Secretary may modify or terminate the agreement if one or more of the following findings
21 is made:
22 (1) Information provided by the debtor in support of the agreement was inaccurate
23 or incomplete.
24 (2) Collection of debt to which the agreement applies is in jeopardy.
25 (3) The debtor's financial condition has changed.
26 (4) The debtor has failed to pay an installment when due.
27 (5) The debtor has failed to provide information requested by the Secretary.
28 The Secretary must give a debtor who has entered into an installment agreement at least 30
29 days' written notice before modifying or terminating the agreement on the grounds that the
30 debtor's financial condition has changed unless the debtor failed to disclose or concealed assets
31 or income when the agreement was made or the debtor has acquired assets since the agreement
32 was made that can satisfy all or part of the debt. A notice must specify the basis for the Secretary's
33 finding of a change in the debtor's financial condition.
34 …
35 "§ 105A-8. Setoff collection; State agency notice, hearing, decision, and refund of
36 setoff.setoff collection.
37 …
38 "§ 105A-8A. Forced collection; prerequisite, State Auditor notice, State Auditor hearing,
39 decision.
40 (a) Prerequisite. – The Office of the State Auditor may not submit notice of final
41 determination of a debt to the Department for forced collection under G.S. 105A-6A(a) until the
42 Auditor has finally determined the debt in accordance with this section. For purposes of this
43 section, a "finally determined" debt shall mean a debt that (i) meets the requirements of
44 G.S. 105A-6A(c), (ii) for which the Auditor has given notice as required by subsection (b) of this
45 section, and (iii) for which the debtor did not file a timely request for hearing under this section,
46 or, for which the debtor did file a timely request for hearing but a decision made after hearing
47 determined that a debtor owed a debt, in a sum certain, to a State agency, and all appellate relief
48 afforded the debtor for purposes of finally determining the debt under this section has been
49 exhausted.
50 (b) Notice. – The Office of the State Auditor must send written notice to a debtor that the
51 Auditor intends to submit the debt owed by the debtor to the Department for forced collection.
