31 "§ 105A-13. Collection assistance fees.
32 (a) State Setoff. Setoff Collection. – To recover the costs incurred by the Department in
33 collecting setoff debts under this Chapter, a collection assistance fee of five dollars ($5.00) is
34 imposed on each debt collected through setoff. The Department must collect this fee as part of
35 the debt and retain it. The collection assistance fee under this subsection shall not be added to
36 child support debts or collected as part of child support debts. Instead, the Department shall retain
37 from collections under Division II of Article 4 of Chapter 105 of the General Statutes the cost of
38 collecting child support debts through debt setoff under this Chapter.
39 (a1) State Forced Collection. – To recover the costs incurred by the Department in force
40 collecting debts under this Chapter, a collection assistance fee equal to three percent (3%) of the
41 amount of the debt is imposed on each debt collected through forced collection. The Department
42 must collect this fee as part of the debt and retain it. The collection assistance fee under this
43 subsection shall not be added to child support debts or collected as part of child support debts.
44 Instead, the Department shall retain from collections under Article 4 of Chapter 105 of the
45 General Statutes the cost of collecting child support debts through forced collection under this
46 Chapter.
47 …
48 (c) Local Debts. – To recover the costs incurred by local agencies in submitting debts for
49 setoff collection under this Chapter, a local collection assistance fee of fifteen dollars ($15.00) is
50 imposed on each local agency debt submitted under G.S. 105A-3(b1) and collected through
House Bill 549-Fifth Edition Page 7

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 setoff. The Department must collect this fee as part of the debt and remit it to the clearinghouse
2 that submitted the debt. The local collection assistance fee does not apply to child support debts.
3 …
4 "§ 105A-14. Accounting Setoff collection; accounting to the claimant agency; agency, credit
5 to debtor's obligation.
6 (a) Setoff Collection; Accounting to Claimant Agency. – Simultaneously with the
7 transmittal of the net proceeds collected through setoff collection to a claimant agency, the
8 Department must provide the agency with an accounting of the setoffs for which payment is
9 being made. The accounting must whenever possible include the full names of the debtors, the
10 debtors' social security numbers or federal identification numbers, the gross proceeds collected
11 per setoff, the net proceeds collected per setoff, and the collection assistance fee added to the
12 debt and collected per setoff.
13 (b) Setoff Collection; Credit to Debtor's Obligation. – Upon receipt by a claimant agency
14 of net proceeds collected on the claimant agency's behalf by the Department, a final
15 determination of the claim if it is a State agency claim, and an accounting of the proceeds as
16 specified under this section, the claimant agency must credit the debtor's obligation with the net
17 proceeds collected.
18 "§ 105A-14A. Forced collection proceeds credited to General Fund.
19 The net proceeds collected through a forced collection conducted under this Chapter shall be
20 credited to the General Fund by the Department within 60 days of collection.
21 …."
22 SECTION 11.(b) This section becomes effective December 1, 2025, and applies to
23 the collection of debts on or after that date.
24 SECTION 12.(a) G.S. 143B-218 reads as rewritten:
25 "§ 143B-218. Department of Revenue – duties.
26 It shall be the duty of the Department to collect and account for the State's tax funds, to insure
27 uniformity of administration of the tax laws and regulations, to conduct research on revenue
28 matters, and to exercise general and specific supervision over the valuation and taxation of
29 property throughout the State.State, and to perform other non-tax related functions as enacted by
30 the General Assembly."
31 SECTION 12.(b) This section becomes effective December 1, 2025, and applies to
32 the performance of non-tax related functions by the Department on or after that date.
